                <head>378. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On August 30 the National Security Council at its 295th meeting discussed the
                    question of United States policy in Southeast Asia with particular reference to
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5612, August 15, “U.S. Policy in
                    Mainland Southeast Asia”. Laos was among the topics in the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> paper and among the topics discussed at the
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> meeting. Both the memorandum of
                    discussion at the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> meeting and <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5612/1, September 5, are printed as <ref
                        target="#d118">Documents 118</ref> and <ref target="#d119">119</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
